# Docs evidence discipline

- Label claims with the master doc's epistemic markers: `[VF]` verified fact (cite the
  primary source), `[EI]` evidence-backed inference, `[TH]` testable hypothesis, `[DD]`
  design decision, `[OQ]` unresolved open question. An unlabeled claim reads as a design
  decision — do not leave verified facts or open questions unlabeled.
- Cite primary sources (official docs, papers, vendor pages), not aggregators. If you could
  not verify something against a primary source, say so explicitly and mark it `[OQ]` or add
  it to `docs/review-queue.md` section 2 — never present it as settled.
- Negative results and dead ends are recorded, not deleted: they go to
  `docs/review-queue.md` section 2.
- `docs/master-doc.md` is byte-identical and hash-pinned. If it appears wrong or stale,
  propose an amendment in `docs/review-queue.md` section 1 (source + proposed change +
  status PROPOSED). Only a human ratifies amendments and re-pins the hash.
- Use relative links (with `#fragments` where useful); `make links` checks them offline.
  When you rename a heading, fix every inbound fragment link in the same change.
